Excellent! We used texas toast, added some nutmeg and vanilla. Cook over medium heat, not high, or the outside will burn before the inside is cooked.

Rating: 4
My father called this the best french toast he ever ate. I used challah and brioche and topped the toasts with sliced strawberries and powdered sugar. They really don't need syrup. Am wondering if other taste combinations would work well too.. maybe substitute frangelico for the orange liquor and sprinkle with nutmeg, or use some other fruit brandy?

